  "prompt": "How can I ask a question without getting marked as \u2018need to improve\u2019?",
  "response": "To ask a question without getting marked as \"need to improve,\" ensure your question is clear, specific, and directly related to the platform\u2019s guidelines or the topic at hand. Here are some tips to craft a well-structured question:\n\n1. **Be Clear and Concise**: Avoid ambiguity or overly complex language. Formulate your question in a way that is easy to understand.\n\n   **Example**: Instead of \u201cWhat\u2019s the thing about the stuff?\u201d ask, \u201cWhat are the key benefits of using renewable energy sources?\u201d\n\n2. **Provide Context**: Include relevant details or background information to help others understand the question better.\n\n   **Example**: Instead of asking, \u201cHow does it work?\u201d ask, \u201cHow does the process of photosynthesis work in plants?\u201d\n\n3. **Stay On Topic**: Ensure your question aligns with the platform\u2019s purpose or the community\u2019s focus. Avoid asking unrelated or off-topic questions.\n\n   **Example**: If you\u2019re on a tech forum, ask, \u201cWhat are the best practices for securing a home Wi-Fi network?\u201d instead of, \u201cWhat\u2019s your favorite recipe?\u201d\n\n4. **Avoid Vague or Open-Ended Questions**: Questions that are too broad or subjective may get marked as needing improvement.\n\n   **Example**: Instead of \u201cWhat do you think about it?\u201d ask, \u201cWhat are the main differences between Python and JavaScript for web development?\u201d\n\n5. **Follow Community Guidelines**: Review the platform\u2019s rules or guidelines to ensure your question meets their standards.\n\nBy being thoughtful and precise, you can increase the likelihood of your question being well-received and answered effectively.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
